The function `atoi` takes a `char *` to translate from ascii to integer, if the `char *` given to `atoi` is `NULL`, its behavior is undefined and can certainly generate a segmentation fault.

If you do not give any argument to your program, `argv[1]` will equal to `NULL`.

Since you are already checking if an argument is given or not, you should provide an else statement to your first condition to remedy this problem like so
```
if (argc &lt; 2) {
    ...
} else {
    size = atoi(argv[1]);
}
```

